The paper deals with the problem of maximizing a non-monotone DR-submodular function subject to a cardinality constraint, which is a problem in combinatorial optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, the paper also mentions that DR-submodularity can be used to solve many machine learning problems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes polynomial-time approximation algorithms, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper also mentions implementing the algorithms on a real-world dataset, which could suggest it belongs to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
